records.addlTxt:
Defendant Norman E Boose in court with attorney Bridget Joy Krause.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for continued sentencing hearing. Letter on behalf of the defendant from Silver Spring Neighborhood Center received and filed. Sentencing hearing proceeded.

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to COUNT 2; credit for 5 days time served. Defendant may have release for work if employed at the time of revocation. Defendant may have release to the Day Reporting Center. 

As to COUNT 2-
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to COUNT 1; Defendant may have release for work if employed at the time of revocation. Defendant may have release to the Day Reporting Center. 

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNT 1 amended and COUNT 2 and placed defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Obtain HSED or diploma;
2) Complete 40 hours of community service;
3) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on COUNT 2 as it is part of a continuous event; 
5) No driving without a valid license;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs and alcohol;
7) Random urine screens;

Court authorized expungment upon successful completion of all conditions of probation.

If revoked, court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid from 25% of funds/earnings. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
